  "text": "Diversity within the R. solanacearum isolates has been studied from decades using techniques such as 16S rRNA, AFLP, RFLP, BOX-PCR, rep-PCR and multiplex PCR [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . Even though these techniques are specific, sensitive and rapid but not free from difficulties such as additional enzymes, instrumentation and high cost, are difficult to adopt in developing countries when screening large number of isolates. However the problem can be overcome by simple repetition of PCR and denaturation of the amplified product by SSCP and LSSP-PCR.",
